# Session-RPC beveiliging (geen quick fixes)

**Lees vóór elke nieuwe read/write op `matches`, `teams`, `users`, `players`, scheids-data of publieke pagina's.**

Architectuurbesluit (custom auth blijft, geen Supabase Auth-migratie): **`custom-auth-architectuur.mdc`**.

Dit project gebruikt **custom auth**: alle REST-requests zijn `anon`. `withUserContext` + `set_config` werkt **niet** betrouwbaar over PostgREST connection pooling. Nieuwe code volgt daarom altijd het session-RPC-model.

Referenties:
- `private.resolve_app_session` — `supabase/migrations/20260610000000_private_resolve_app_session.sql`
- Publiek: `get_public_matches` / `get_public_teams` — `20260611000000_public_schedule_rpcs.sql`
- Scheids: `src/services/scheidsrechter/scheidsSessionFetch.ts`
- Teams ingelogd: `src/services/core/teamsSessionFetch.ts`
- Publiek client: `src/services/public/publicScheduleFetch.ts`
- Verificatie: `npm run test:security`

## Beslisboom (verplicht)

| Wie | Wat | Hoe |
|-----|-----|-----|
| **Anon** (geen login) | Speelschema, standen, teamnamen | `get_public_matches()` / `get_public_teams()` — expliciete kolom-allowlist |
| **Ingelogd** (admin/referee/manager) | Rol-gevoelige reads/writes | `p_session_token` + `private.resolve_app_session` in **één transactie** |
| **Intern in DEFINER-RPC** | Teamnamen joinen | `JOIN public.teams` — nooit `*_public` views |

```typescript
// Publiek
import { fetchPublicMatches, fetchPublicTeams } from '@/services/public/publicScheduleFetch';

// Ingelogd
import { getRpcSessionArgs } from '@/lib/authSession';
supabase.rpc('get_teams_for_session', { ...getRpcSessionArgs(), p_team_id: id });
```

## Verboden quick fixes (nooit introduceren)

- `CREATE VIEW …_public` + `GRANT SELECT TO anon` — omzeilt RLS (`security_invoker = false` is geen oplossing)
- `referees_public`, `teams_public`, `matches_public`, `players_public` of varianten
- RPC met client-provided `p_user_id`, `p_admin_user_id`, `p_role` zonder sessie-validatie
- Nieuwe `withUserContext` voor reads die session-RPC kunnen zijn
- Publieke `from('matches')` / `from('users')` in `src/components/pages/public/**`
- `USING (true)` SELECT policies op gevoelige tabellen
- Anon-exposure van JSONB line-ups, contact-PII, of `assigned_referee_id`

**Als iets “even snel” anon-leesbaar moet:** nieuwe `SECURITY DEFINER` RPC met vaste `RETURNS TABLE` — geen view.

## Nieuwe database-RPC (template)

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_<resource>_for_session(p_session_token uuid, ...)
RETURNS TABLE(...)
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path TO 'public', 'private'
AS $$
DECLARE v_role text;
BEGIN
  SELECT s.role INTO v_role
  FROM private.resolve_app_session(p_session_token) s LIMIT 1;
  IF v_role IS NULL OR v_role NOT IN ('admin', ...) THEN RETURN; END IF;
  RETURN QUERY SELECT ...;
END;
$$;
REVOKE ALL ON FUNCTION public.get_<resource>_for_session(...) FROM PUBLIC;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.get_<resource>_for_session(...) TO anon;

-- Daarna lint 0028: invoker wrapper (zie 20260615020000)
-- SELECT private.create_public_invoker_wrapper('public.get_<resource>_for_session(...)'::regprocedure);
-- REVOKE EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.get_<resource>_for_session(...) FROM authenticated;
```

Publieke anon-RPC (zonder sessie): `SET search_path TO 'public'`, alleen niet-gevoelige kolommen, expliciete `::text` casts.

## Nieuwe client-feature (checklist)

- [ ] Geen `from('*_public')` of nieuwe bypass-view
- [ ] Publiek → `publicScheduleFetch`; ingelogd → `*SessionFetch` + `getRpcSessionArgs()`
- [ ] `enabled: !!getSessionToken()` voor session-queries; publiek zonder token
- [ ] `staleTime: 0`, `refetchOnMount: 'always'` (zie `data-snel-laden.mdc`)
- [ ] Types in `src/integrations/supabase/types.ts` bijgewerkt
- [ ] `scripts/test-matches-security.sh` uitgebreid indien nieuwe anon/sessie-grens
- [ ] `npm run test:security` groen na deploy

## Deploy-volgorde (geen regressies)

1. Nieuwe RPC's aanmaken
2. Interne RPC's ontkoppelen van views (join `teams` direct)
3. Client migreren
4. Views droppen (`REVOKE` + `DROP`)
5. `supabase db query --linked -f supabase/migrations/<file>.sql` per migratie

**Nooit** views droppen vóór client + RPC's live zijn.
